searchParameters.q: how much is a 1964 d nickel worth

answerBox.snippet: In circulated condition, a 1964 D Jefferson nickel will pull in $0.10 to $0.2. One graded MS65 is worth $15, while one graded MS67 can bring in as much as $600. A Full Step 1964 nickel-graded MS65 is worth about $700, while one graded MS66 can fetch $4,250. Full-step proof-like 1964 nickels are extremely rare.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What makes the 1964 D nickel rare?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The 1964-D Jefferson Nickel has the highest mintage for any Nickel ever struck by the U.S. Mint. This was also the first year in which the mint struck over a billion Nickels for any date. Compare this to the 1950-D Jefferson Nickel which has a mintage of 2,630,000.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell a 1964 special strike nickel?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The 1964 Special Strike Jefferson Nickels usually display an extremely sharp strike, as well as having sharp and square edge rims. The surfaces feature a Satin like appearance. However, the coins are not circulation strikes, nor are they proofs, hence, the coins are referred to as Special Strikes.
